e Update Task-S-1-5-21-3445421715-2530590580-3149308974-1193` preserves the deleted user's SID and confirms the account existed.\n\nMcAfee VirusScan Enterprise 8.8 was installed on the host but **did not detect the keylogger** — `McShield.evtx` is empty (0 records) and `C:\\Quarantine\\` is empty.\n\nBeginning **2020-02-22**, the **shieldbase** Incident Response team — chiefly user `cbarton-a` from threat-hunting workstations `BASE-HUNT-02` and `BASE-HUNT-03` — performed repeated authenticated **F-Response Subject** + **Mnemosyne** memory/disk acquisitions against this host. This was preceded on **2020-02-17 08:00:37 UTC** by a Group Policy Restricted-Groups change that added domain SID …-1212 to the local `Builtin\\Administrators` group (consistent with provisioning IR access). The volume image being analysed is the artefact of the most recent F-Response collection (2021-09-16).\n\nConfidence in the keylogger finding is **Confirmed**: the malware family is named in plaintext inside `install.log` and the on-disk file layout exactly matches the published BlazingTools \"Perfect Keylogger\" component set.\n\n---\n\n## 02 Evidence Examined\n\n| Evidence ID | Source Path | Type | Size | Verification |\n|-------------|-------------|------|------|--------------|\n| EVID-001 | `/cases/Test1/base-wkstn-01-c-drive.E01` | E01 (single NTFS volume — no MBR) | 31 GiB | `ewfverify` SUCCESS, MD5 + SHA1 match acquisition (`fd463e4e…`, `c4e37e7f…`) |\n\nMounted read-only via:\n\n```\newfmount → /mnt/ewf_wkstn01/ewf1\nmount -o ro,loop,noatime,offset=0 → /mnt/wkstn01\n```\n\nRecorded in `/cases/Test1/analysis/mounts.csv`.\n\nThe acquired image is a **C: volume only** (`fsstat` shows OEM `NTFS`, version `Windows XP`, MFT first-cluster 786432); there is no partition table. The image was originally acquired with FTK Imager identified as \"base-wkstn-01 c-drive\", case 001.\n\n---\n\n## 03 System Profile\n\n| Property | Value |\n|----------|-------|\n| Hostname | `BASE-WKSTN-01` |\n| FQDN 