tr>\n    <tr><td><code>perfmon-kr.exe</code></td><td>2017-08-31 17:30:35</td><td><strong>2018-08-31 21:39:35</strong></td><td>148043</td></tr>\n    <tr><td><code>perfmon-kvw.exe</code></td><td>2017-08-31 17:30:35</td><td><strong>2018-08-31 21:39:35</strong></td><td>148040</td></tr>\n    <tr><td><code>perfmon-kwb.dll</code></td><td>2017-08-31 17:30:35</td><td><strong>2018-08-31 21:39:35</strong></td><td>148041</td></tr>\n    <tr><td><code>pkl.bin</code></td><td>2017-08-31 17:39:19</td><td><strong>2018-08-31 21:42:43</strong></td><td>3134</td></tr>\n    <tr><td><code>web.dt</code></td><td>2017-08-31 17:33:47</td><td><strong>2018-08-31 21:42:47</strong></td><td>120226</td></tr>\n    <tr><td><code>opt.dat</code></td><td>2017-08-31 17:39:03</td><td><strong>2018-08-31 21:48:03</strong></td><td>120972</td></tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The exact one-year date offset and consistent hour-of-day delta indicate the operator used a SI-timestomp tool\nsuch as <em>SetMACE</em>, <em>timestomp.exe</em>, or an equivalent PowerShell routine. The FN timestamps preserve ground truth\nbecause they cannot be modified via standard Windows APIs.</p>\n\n<p><strong>YARA confirmation:</strong> rule <code>BlazingTools_Perfect_Keylogger_Install_Log</code> matched\n<code>install.log</code> (<code>/cases/Test1/exports/yara_hits.csv</code>).</p>\n\n<p><strong>Alternative explanations considered.</strong> A legitimate &ldquo;PerfMon K-edition&rdquo; performance tool\n&mdash; <span class=\"badge badge-benign\">Rejected</span> &mdash; the plaintext BlazingTools marker and exact PKL component\nnaming convention rule this out. IR-team-planted analysis sample &mdash; not supported because the files predate the\nIR-collection campaign by 18 months and use an attacker-style drop path (Edge download &rarr; user Temp &rarr; ProgramData).</p>\n\n<p><strong>Persistence: Hypothesis.</strong> No keylogger entry was found in <code>HKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run</code>,\nthe correspond