le>\n\n<p>The <code>spsql</code> user profile has been removed from this host. The only surviving SID reference is the file\n<code>C:\\Windows\\System32\\Tasks\\OneDrive Standalone Update Task-S-1-5-21-3445421715-2530590580-3149308974-1193</code>\ndated 2018-08-31, which preserves the deleted user&rsquo;s SID-to-presence binding.</p>\n\n<h3>F-03 &mdash; Anti-forensic tradecraft</h3>\n<p>Confidence: <strong>Confirmed</strong>. Three concurrent behaviours: (a) one-year SI&nbsp;timestomp on all keylogger files\n(see F-01), (b) <code>spsql</code> user-profile removal, eliminating NTUSER.DAT / browser history / ShellBags / JumpLists / RecentDocs,\nand (c) a backdated PE LinkDate on the downloaded <code>k.exe</code> (reports 2010-02-10).</p>\n\n<h3>F-04 &mdash; Local-Administrators escalation (likely IR provisioning)</h3>\n<p>Confidence: <strong>Probable</strong> (legitimate). One EID-4732 (&ldquo;Member added to security-enabled local group&rdquo;) fired in the entire ~3.5-year log:</p>\n<table>\n  <thead><tr><th>UTC</th><th>Subject</th><th>Group</th><th>Added member SID</th></tr></thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr><td>2020-02-17 08:00:37</td><td><code>shieldbase\\BASE-WKSTN-01$</code> (SYSTEM, <code>0x3E7</code>)</td><td><code>Builtin\\Administrators</code></td><td><code>S-1-5-21-3445421715-2530590580-3149308974-1212</code></td></tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The computer-account / SYSTEM subject and the absence of any interactive logon by that SID is consistent with GPO\nRestricted-Groups. Five days later <code>cbarton-a</code> began deploying F-Response (F-05). Identity of SID&hellip;-1212\nrequires AD lookup. Alternative explanation: attacker GPO write &mdash; weaker because only one such event exists in the log\nand a documented IR-collection campaign followed shortly after.</p>\n\n<h3>F-05 &mdash; Documented IR collection (2020-02 to 2021-09)</h3>\n<p>Confidence: <strong>Confirmed</strong>. Service installs (Security EID 4697, System EID 7045):</p>\n<table>\n  <thead><tr>