tr>\n    <tr><td>7</td><td><code>*\\C$</code></td><td><code>BASE-HUNT-03$</code></td><td>172.16.5.28</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>4</td><td><code>*\\ADMIN$</code></td><td><code>cbarton-a</code></td><td>172.16.5.25</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>2</td><td><code>*\\IPC$</code></td><td><strong><code>spadertech\\pman.adm</code></strong></td><td>172.16.6.17</td></tr>\n    <tr><td>1</td><td><code>*\\ADMIN$</code></td><td><code>BASE-HUNT-02$</code></td><td>172.16.5.27</td></tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The <code>TempFRes</code> share is created by F-Response during forensic collection. The single cross-domain account\n<code>spadertech\\pman.adm</code> warrants customer validation (2 IPC$ hits only).</p>\n\n<h3>F-06 &mdash; Kansa PowerShell IR collection (2018-08-15)</h3>\n<p>Confidence: <strong>Confirmed</strong>. <code>Microsoft-Windows-PowerShell/Operational</code> contains 1,218\nEID-4104 script-block events including <code>Get-Tasklistv.ps1</code>, <code>Get-ProcsWMI.ps1</code> and the\n<code>Kansa.ps1 output directive follows</code> marker. Ran <strong>16 days before</strong> the keylogger install &mdash;\nnot indicative of active compromise at that point.</p>\n\n<h3>F-07 &mdash; High-volume WinRM is Windows Event Forwarding (benign)</h3>\n<p>Confidence: <strong>Confirmed</strong>. 210,037 EID-145 events of which 209,791 enumerate the\n<code>SubscriptionManager/Subscription</code> resource URI on an 85-second cadence &mdash; classic WEF heartbeat.</p>\n\n<h3>F-08 &mdash; AV bypass</h3>\n<p>Confidence: <strong>Confirmed</strong>. <code>McShield.evtx</code> contains 0 records; <code>C:\\Quarantine\\</code> is empty;\nno <code>Application.evtx</code> events name the BlazingTools components. The keylogger evaded McAfee for the full 3+ years.</p>\n\n<h3>F-09 &mdash; Local <code>range_admin</code> account</h3>\n<p>Confidence: <strong>Probable</strong> (cyber-range baseline artefact). SAM RID 1003 in Administrators group;\npassword set 2018-08-29 (two days before the spsql incident); <st